Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.values.version

Class Version

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.values.version.Version
  • public class Version
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a semantic version, such as "6.3" or "1.2.1" or "6.3-rc". Supports major(), minor(), patch() and release() values.

    Parsing

    Versions can be created by parsing a String with parse(String) as well as by using the of() factory methods, passing in major, minor, patch and release values.

    Information

    • major() - The major version
    • minor() - The minor version
    • patch() - The optional 'dot' revision, or NO_REVISION if there is none
    • release() - The release name, or null if there is none
    • hasPatch() - True if this version has a revision value
    • hasRelease() - True if this version has a release name

    Functional

    • withoutPatch() - This version without the revision value
    • withoutRelease() - This version without the release name

    Comparison

    • #equals(Object) - True if the versions are equal
    • isNewerThan(Version) - True if this version is newer than the given version
    • isNewerThanOrEqualTo(Version) - True if this version is newer than or the same as the given version
    • isOlderThan(Version) - True if this version is older than the given version
    • isOlderThanOrEqualTo(Version) - True if this version is older than or the same as the given version
    • newer(Version) - The newer of this version and the given version
    • older(Version) - The older of this version and the given version

    Version objects implement the hashCode() / equals(Object) contract.

    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
    See Also:
    *Semantic Versioning*
